-- Dubai's Landmark May List Shares in Saudi Arabia, The National Says
-- B y   S t e f a n i a   B i a n c h i
-- 2010-10-28T04:32:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-28/dubai-s-landmark-may-list-shares-in-saudi-arabia-the-national-says.html
Landmark Group, the Dubai-based
retail company, may sell shares to the public and list on the
Saudi stock exchange, The National newspaper reported, citing
Micky Jagtiani, the company’s chairman and owner.  Landmark, which agreed to buy Carluccio’s Plc for 90.3
million pounds ($138.9 million) in September, may also list
shares in Dubai and India at a later date, the newspaper
reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stefania Bianchi in Dubai at 
